LAGOS – The annual Squash Ladder Challenge of the Squash Section of the Lagos Country Club saw Dr. Olubunmi Apata on top of the Gold Ladder scoring 93 points from 24 matches.The tournament sponsored by Swifta Systems and Services limited recorded over 500 matches played amongst 47 participants within two weeks. The intensive game also saw Deji Sule topped the ladder in the Veteran category, Dimeji Dare- William won The Most Improved Player of the tournament while Giwa Oladapo won the prize for playing more matches than all those who entered the competition. Speaking at a brief prize-giving ceremony, Kemi Orelaja, Head of Sales, Swifta, acknowledged the bonding value of the competition, stating that all through, the competition was not only healthy but fun. As a Tech company that is in touch with the future, he expressed optimism that future tournaments will be greater than the current one. He also stated the company’s resolve and mission to add value and be a problem solver on IT and ancillary solutions. Sir Semoore Badejo, Chairman of Squash Section, Lagos Country Club, appreciated the Sponsor and looked forward to a mutually beneficial relationship with the Company on a long term basis. He said that he is looking forward to next year when the annual tournament is expected to be bigger with more participating members.